modules.description: Transforms Yocaml programs into Lwt-based computations, enabling asynchronous execution. It provides primitives for logging, file system operations, directory management, content hashing, and process execution, all returning values wrapped in an effect type `t`. These operations work with paths, strings, timestamps, and process results, supporting tasks like reading and writing files, checking file existence, and running external commands with customizable success checks.

This module defines the essential interfaces for building a Git runtime in YOCaml. It specifies the `SOURCE` and `CONFIG` module types, which describe the expected structure of source data and configuration parameters needed to generate artifacts in a Git database. These interfaces are used to ensure consistency when constructing runtimes that produce version-controlled output for deployment in environments like Unikernels.

This module executes YOCAML programs using a Git store as a compilation target, comparing generated artifacts with a remote repository and committing and pushing changes. It works with Git databases, source runtimes, and Lwt-based effectful computations, handling version-controlled output for deployment. Concrete use cases include building and synchronizing static sites or configuration files in a Unikernel environment using Git as the backend.
